Abdul Haji might be the first member of the Kenyan senate to be elected unopposed. Haji, the son of the late Garissa senator Yusuf haji and brother to the director of public prosecutions Noordin haji has received unanimous endorsement by political stakeholders in the county of Garissa to take over his father&rsquo;s constituency. Interested political parties intending to hold nominations in byelections scheduled for may 5th had until the close of business today to submit the names of the aspirants and the preferred dates for primaries.